Components & credits
--------------------
* PS5 Image Studio GUI (the `lazy_studio` package) — the CustomTkinter
  workstation interface.
* LazyMkPFS backend (the `lazy_mkpfs` package) by Nazky — the underlying
  exFAT / FFPFSC build, packing, and verification pipeline that does the heavy
  lifting. PS5 Image Studio is a graphical front-end over this backend.

Third-party
-----------
* CustomTkinter — UI toolkit (MIT).
* cryptography — used by the backend (Apache-2.0 / BSD).
* Optional fast backends (isal, zlib-ng) when present — accelerated
  (de)compression.

Runtime tools the Linux build shells out to (not bundled):
* mkfs.exfat (exfatprogs), losetup / mount / umount (util-linux), tkinter
  (python3-tk).

This is a free, community tool for PS5 homebrew use. Use at your own risk.
